Detailed Description

Contains phone state and service related information.

Contains phone state and service related information. Programmer can always get ServiceState through PhoneStateListener The following phone information is included in returned ServiceState:

  • Service state: IN_SERVICE, OUT_OF_SERVICE, EMERGENCY_ONLY, POWER_OFF
  • Roaming indicator
  • Operator name, short name and numeric id
  • Network selection mode 
 // MyPhoneStateListener is derived from PhoneStateListener
 void MyPhoneStateListener::onServiceStateChanged(const gaia::telephony::ServiceState& serviceState){
     serviceState.getState();
 }

enum gaia::telephony::ServiceState::STATE

State.

Enumerator:
STATE_IN_SERVICE 

Normal operation condition, the phone is registered with an operator either in home network or in roaming.

STATE_OUT_OF_SERVICE 

Phone is not registered with any operator, the phone can be currently searching a new operator to register to, or not searching to registration at all, or registration is denied, or radio signal is not available.

STATE_EMERGENCY_ONLY 

The phone is registered and locked.

Only emergency numbers are allowed.

STATE_POWER_OFF 

Radio of telephony is explicitly powered off.

gaia::base::String gaia::telephony::ServiceState::getOperatorAlphaLong ( ) const

Get current registered operator name in long alphanumeric format.

In GSM/UMTS, long format can be up to 16 characters long. In CDMA, returns the ERI text, if set. Otherwise, returns the ONS.

Returns:
long name of operator, null if unregistered or unknown
gaia::base::String gaia::telephony::ServiceState::getOperatorAlphaShort ( ) const

Get current registered operator name in short alphanumeric format.

gaia::base::String gaia::telephony::ServiceState::getOperatorNumeric ( ) const

Get current registered operator numeric id.

In GSM/UMTS, numeric format is 3 digit country code plus 2 or 3 digit network code.

numeric format of operator, null if unregistered or unknown
